  "body": "### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a status-go :), I want to know when device network goes offline, switches networks, using expensive connection or on the poor quality network. I want to be notified by calling my `ConnectionChange()` API method.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n*Summary*: Implement event listener as described in https://facebook.github.io/react-native/docs/netinfo.html (example doc, feel free to use better/proper docs/approaches) and call `ConnectionChange(type string, expensive bool)` call from `status-go` API (shall be available in nightly build). `type` is mirroring type from RN docs for simplicity.\r\n\r\nThe corresponding PR in status go: https://github.com/status-im/status-go/pull/649\r\n\r\nCurrently, status-go should print network state changes into logs. The more advanced logic for handling different network switch cases will be implemented in the follow-up issues.\r\n",
